This book will be written in docbook format

It aims to provide agile engineering training after CSM training to gain real development experience

Big thanks to Tim O'Brien to let me reuse his template (no matter I can complete this manual or not)

Project:
It is a leagcy GUI admin system, and want to be more ...
Two or three teams work on same tasks to see challenge result??

day 1: establish the agile environment: 
(scrum, continuous integration, version control system and prepare for the project)
09:00-10:00, Introduction, Scrum, seperate into teams
10:00-12:00, version control svn, eclipse setup, maven
12:00-13:00, lunch
13:00-15:00, install hudson CI
15:00-15:15, break
15:15-17:00, install nexus, 3pp
17:00-17:30, Quick review, summary, and the project introduction)

day 2: Iteration 1, quality on the wall

09:00-10:00, planning meeting 1, 2

(refactory, junit, coverage, JIRA system )

day 3: TDD, quality control : PMD, FindBugs, coverage, SONAR
09:00-10:00 daily scrum meeting
review and quick retrospective
15:00-16:00, review meeting
16:00-17:00, retrospective

day 4: collaboration with mylyn (trac), frequent release, package: maven respository more
day 5: ??? 

